 Some palaeographical features:
  ሎ has the loop, of circular or triangular shape, marking the 7th order sometimes attached directly to the body of the letter, sometimes attached 
  through a linking line of various lenght (cp. 113);  
  the upper part of some letters, e.g. ቆ, ቶ, የ, ደ, ጸ has a triangular shape; 
  letters ሀ, መ, ሠ, ወ, ዐ are of angular shape; 
  letters ሰ, በ, ፀ are squared; 
  the pipe of letters ም, ሥ, ዎ, ዖ is slanted; 
  the pipes of the letter ለ are paired and their connection is sometimes angular and sometimes curved; 
  the right loop of ሞ does not rest on the ruled line ; 
  the pipe of the letters ሣ and ገ is slanted to the left; 
  the 1st and the 6th orders of the letter ሰ can hardly be distinguished; 
  the letter ቍ has no linking line; 
  numerals are written without dashes; 
  ፩ looks like ፬;
  ፪ has angular and not separated loops;
  ፮ has the loop open, looking like "compressed" ፯;
  ፱ is of angular shape; 
  the upper part of ፻ has an angular shape; 
  the crux ansata in used, e.g., on .
On the features of this manuscript, see 112-114.
